ExecDesc.value: Apple Quicktime MJPEG Frame stsd Atom Heap Overflow

EngDesc.value: A heap overflow vulnerability exists in Apple Quicktime. The vulnerability is due to improper processing of mjpeg movies with an improper jpeg frame size in the stsd atom. This vulnerability can be exploited by a remote attacker by enticing the target user to open a specially crafted file with the affected application. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the currently logged-in user.
